Two files have the same function with the same bug:

1. platform/cli/src/commands/config.ts lines 293-297 (`resolveStoredPluginPath`):
```typescript
if (storedPath.startsWith('/')) return storedPath;
if (storedPath.startsWith('~/')) return resolve(homedir(), storedPath.slice(2));
return resolve(configDir, storedPath);
```

2. platform/plugin-tools/src/commands/build.ts lines 107-111 (`resolvePluginPathForComparison`):
```typescript
if (storedPath.startsWith('/')) return storedPath;
if (storedPath.startsWith('~/')) return resolve(homedir(), storedPath.slice(2));
return resolve(configDir, storedPath);
```

Both miss Windows-style tilde paths. On Windows, a path might be stored as `~\my-plugin`. Fix: add a check for `startsWith('~\\')` (escaped backslash) in addition to `startsWith('~/')`. Also handle Windows absolute paths (e.g., `C:\...`) in config.ts — the build.ts version doesn't check for Windows absolute paths either, but the `resolve()` fallback handles them correctly since `path.resolve` treats drive-letter paths as absolute.

Note: platform/mcp-server/src/config.ts also has `isLocalPathEntry` (line 110-117) which already handles both `~/` and backslash variants correctly — use that as the reference pattern.
